title: Recording audio at gigs.
description:
Since August last year I have used a Panasonic GH5 to record gigs at out local club. I have used a Zoom H1 to record the audio since 2014. In this video I collaborated with the band 'Freshly Cut Grass' for them to provide a mix of their disk recorded audio, what a difference that made!

The 'desk' recorded sound looks like it's clipping on the vu meter, it is not, I checked in Adobe Audition.

title: Garden Bird Feeder, Lumix GH5 video test
description:
My first video test of the Lumix GH5 filming our bird feeder. I used 6K with the non-anamorphic 12-60mm Leica lens at 4:3 ratio and cropped to 4K 16:9. This is potentially a good setting for me, videoing live jam sessions, as I will be able to crop without losing much of the full frame quality.

The video was recorded as 4:3 4992x3744 pixels and cropped to 3840x2160.

title: Dave Brubeck: Take 5 performed in 1972 - HQ Stereo Sound
description:
Dave Brubeck, Gerry Mulligan, Paul Desmond, Alan Dawson and Jack Six performing Take 5 at the Philharmonic in Berlin on 4 November 1972.

I found a copy of this video on YouTube and realised it was the exact same version as that from 'We're All Together Again for the First Time’, one of my favourite Brubeck albums - so I decided to have a go at synchronising the audio from my CD. Not an easy task as they were different lengths (I listened to both audio tracks simultaneously and altered the video to fit the CD sound when I heard phase shift). The video quality was not great to begin with but I am delighted that I found it.
